{{Underline|F4F0EC}}
<center>I woke up from that [[Level 245|sleepy hollow]].</center>


<center>I remember few memories about that place.</center>


<center>I barely remember anything, my experience in the level, the level I was prior to entering it, why I was even in the level, what the level even looked like.</center>


<center>But I know one thing for certain.</center>


<center>Whatever location that I am currently in right now, is not the same as the one where I fell asleep.</center>


<center>This place... is odd, to say the least.</center>


<center>I may not know too much of that place, but I know for certain that it had commie blocks and cold weather.</center>


<center>This new place, is barren, dry, and without human structures in sight.</center>


<center>Everywhere I look, I spot dead trees, endless desert, trail marks, white sand, and... unusually overcast skies?</center>


<center>After some time, I became overpowered by an overwhelming determination to stand up and move forward.</center>


<center>Curiosity then followed suit, and the culmination of both resulted in me eventually standing up and pacing forward.</center>


<center>I embarked on an adventure, on a straight line, with nothing to stop me.</center>


<center>I continued to walk...</center>


<center><span style="color:gainsboro">and walk...</span></center>


<center><span style="color:silver">and walk...</span></center>






<center>I walked for ten minutes now. The more I walk, the foggier my surroundings get.</center>


<center>Weirdly enough, I cannot exhaust myself of energy from this intense walking.</center>


<center>And this undying urge to keep walking further only grows.</center>


<center>As I continue to venture out further, I notice a distinct outline in the fog.</center>


<center>It looks like a tall, neverending tower.</center>


<center>However, I can't really make any distinct shape out of it. There is only one way to reveal its true nature; by moving forward.</center>



<center><div class="image">[[File:Biblelevelimg.jpg|260px|link=]]</div></center>



<center>What?</center>


<center>That's the Tower of Babel! I remember learning about this thing in my Bible studies back in [[the Frontrooms]].</center>


<center>Man constructed a megalopolis with a spire that threatened to transpierce heaven itself. God -after seeing what He considered a monstrosity- jumbled up the languages and cultures of mankind so that they would never achieve what they had through unity again.</center>


<center>God ''thought'' that this monstrous conglomeration was the limit of what we would achieve.</center>


<center>''A wave of memories rush through me like rapids, each memory like a riptide threatening to drown me.''</center>


<center>As my mind starts to get back on its feet, many thoughts start to pop up in my head.</center>


<center>''What if God banished the city and tower to the Backrooms, along with its laborers and residents?''</center>


<center>''What happened to the city and tower, its residents, after millennia of rotting in the Backrooms?''</center>


<center>''Are there even any residents within the city anymore? Is there even a city? Is a heaven-piercing spectacle all that remains?''</center>


<center>Curiosity has gotten the best of me. To answer all these questions, I could once again just walk closer, as I still feel compelled to do so...</center>




<center>It's been an hour and a half. The more I walk into this biblical landscape, the more uncanny it gets.</center>


<center>The dust obscures my vision more, sound is becoming more distorted, the Tower of Babel's silhouette contrasts from the background more, taking on a reddish hue, my surroundings start glitching out... </center>


<center>My determination to continue walking surges in me. It is the most motivated and driven I have been in a long time.</center>


<center>And my immediate reaction is to follow these instincts.</center>


<center>As I continue walking, I find... peculiar sights. I see expeditioners from various groups laying dead, alongside their broken equipment.</center>


<center>I feel as if many have tried documenting this level, and ultimately failed, and that it may be the end of the line for me soon.</center>


<center>But even after two grueling hours, I still continue walking.</center>


<center>I notice something is up with the Tower of Babel as I slowly approach it. I can now distinguish the structure's minor details, no longer just being a mere silhouette.</center>


<center>As I take a closer look at it, I notice that the demented wrath of the Backrooms has taken over it.</center>


<center>I look closely, and various parts of the megalophobic conglomeration appear glitching out.</center>


<center>Shortly after, I notice human beings appearing in the distance. It must be the inhabitants of what this city once was.</center>


<center>They frantically frolick around, acting like mere animals. They mumble gibberish and perform unusual acts.</center>


<center>They don't even look like humans. Upon closer inspection, they resemble [[Entity 9|Facelings]] more. It could be that they once were humans which were corrupted into Facelings by the lunatic nature of the Backrooms.</center>


<center>As I watch the obscene sights unfurl around me, I continue walking, for they do no harm for me as of the moment.</center>


<center>I start seeing buildings around me. They are devoid of any life.</center>


<center>It is also weird how there are buildings everywhere now, except for the path that I am currently on.</center>


<center>I think the level itself wants me to go on an adventure.</center>


<center>But then I feel it. The feeling that I have come farther than many.</center>


<center>The devolved facelings also aren't disrupting my path. In fact, I almost feel welcomed here.</center>


<center>I stare at the glory of the tower.</center>


<center>At its base, a massive door awaits.</center>


<center>Sealed is my fate, to pass through such a gate.</center>


<center>My dedication to continue walking reaches its peak.</center>


<center>And even if the situation feels bleak,</center>


<center>I have one clear mission for today.</center>


<center>I must approach that door, with no delay.</center>


<center>Eventually, the door starts opening slowly.</center>


<center>As the massive doors slowly opens up,</center>


<center>it reveals a glimpse...</center>


<center>[[Level 1000|<span style="font-family:Rubik Glitch; background:linear-gradient(to right, indigo, crimson, darkmagenta);  -webkit-background-clip:text !important; -webkit-text-fill-color: transparent; text-shadow: thistle 0px 0px 8.25px">...of what lies beyond.</span>]]</center>


